modern classic of building construction literature. In the USA, it is used as a reference work for many architectural courses. With the chapters "Material", "Wall", "Roof", "Structure", "Environment" and "Applications" it systematically explores the subject and provides a clear and efficient structure to the reader.For the fourth edition, many of the 3D illustrations have been updated and, likewise, the technical information has been brought up to date. "Applications" showcases current developments, such as those relating to mass customization manufacture of components, and presents material and construction innovations. A compact and systematic handbook filled with information, produced for students and young architects alike.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aArchitecturexDetails. 0aBuildingvHandbooks, manuals, etc. 0aBuilding. 4aAndrew Watts. 4aArchitektur. 4aBaukonstruktion. 4aHandbuch. 4aInnovation. 7aARCHITECTURE / Methods & Materials.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2016z9783110482812oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978303560771040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783035607710423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783035607710.jpg  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_AD  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_AD  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DADb2016  aZDB-23-DGGb2016